About
This repository contains my notes and practice problems from AMS210: Linear Algebra.
The course covered the fundamental concepts of linear algebra, including matrices, systems of linear equations, vector spaces, linear transformations, orthogonality, and eigenvalues. I created this repository to organize what I learned throughout the semester and to use it as a reference for future computer science courses.
Topics Covered
Systems of Linear Equations
* Gaussian Elimination
* Row Reduction
* Echelon Form
* Reduced Row Echelon Form (RREF)
Matrices
* Matrix Operations
* Matrix Multiplication
* Matrix Inverse
* Identity Matrix
* Elementary Matrices
Determinants
* Cofactor Expansion
* Properties of Determinants
* Invertibility
Vector Spaces
* Vectors
* Linear Combinations
* Span
* Linear Independence
* Basis
* Dimension
Linear Transformations
* Matrix Representation
* Kernel (Null Space)
* Image (Column Space)
* Rank
* Nullity
Orthogonality
* Dot Product
* Orthogonal Vectors
* Orthogonal Projection
* Orthonormal Basis
* Gram-Schmidt Process
Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors
* Characteristic Polynomial
* Eigenvalues
* Eigenvectors
* Diagonalization
What I Learned
After completing this course, I can:
* Solve systems of linear equations using matrix methods.
* Perform matrix operations and determine matrix invertibility.
* Understand vector spaces, basis, and linear independence.
* Compute eigenvalues and eigenvectors.
* Apply linear algebra concepts that are commonly used in computer science.


Future Plans
I plan to continue updating this repository as I learn more advanced topics related to linear algebra, including numerical methods, singular value decomposition (SVD), principal component analysis (PCA), and their applications in machine learning and computer graphics.
